messages.subject: Re: [Unschooling-dotcom] 29 is still little, hee hee(was Re: 7 is still little.)
messages.msgSnippet: Yea Aimee! What a delight you must be for you children! I never had that as a child, my parents were not in good health. Laurie ... From: AimeeL73@cs.com To:
messages.messageBody:
Yea Aimee! What a delight you must be for you children! I never had that as a child, my parents were not in good health. Laurie
----- Original Message -----
From: AimeeL73@...
To: Unschooling-dotcom@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Saturday, May 31, 2003 12:40 PM
Subject: Re: [Unschooling-dotcom] 29 is still little, hee hee(was Re: 7 is still little.)


kellibac@... writes:

<< my most cherished times are when I can "be a kid" with my kids on the
floor, at the park ect. Childhood was not long enough for me. I'm going back....
Kelli
>>

How come I am always the only parent going down the slide at the playground?
hehehe
They had a really cool plastic rock climbing thingy too, that was fun. All
the other parents sat on their benches, bored, yelling at their kids
occasionally, and of course, looking at me like I was crazy. Is there an age limit I
don't know about? lol

~Aimee
